caption: Great food! They always have very fresh fish and the mole enchiladas are to die for. In the summertime head to the rooftop bar for a pitcher of margaritas and ceviche.

Very cute restaurant - upstairs patio is nice and well ventilated. The barman made great suggestions & didn't skimp on the alcohol. Food was a little dry but they brought extra sauces when we asked. Tasted quite authentic which was a nice change from standard TexMex
Best margaritas and bartenders in town!
Good food, good service, socially distanced tables. It's all good.
Cool spot! Margaritas were great and the mole sauce was incredible
I like this venue a lot. there is a very nice spirit. The kitcen is great. the service is effective and the stuff is professional. The cost is decent. I warmly recommend.
Finest food, welcoming employees, regularly excellent ambience. They charge affordable prices and the food quality is excellent. Keep it up.
Best Mexican food, margaritas, atmosphere, and service in the area!!! 😍😍😍
Authentic and delicious!!
Late lunch. Magaritas were decent and food was good.  Made for a pleasant afternoon.
Great food. Good chips. Upstairs seating reminds me of Mexico: roofed, but open (with ceiling fans, don't worry). The Enchiladas Suizas were excellent.
Good Mexican restaurant with very authentic looking environment. Nice drinks and food.

Nice people, but this is not Mexican food. The salsa is the same chunky stuff you buy in a jar at the store and the rice is the same as instant rice you can buy out of a bag. I ordered a beef burrito and they brought me a steak fajita wrapped in a tortilla with the instant rice inside.
Enjoyed the roof top atmosphere last night and great company. It's so nice to have the option to sit outside even if there's a roof, especially when the weather is accommodating.
Great food and venue to host private events!

Our meal here last night was fantastic! Our table particularly enjoyed the salsa, which was thick and mild. I would be comfortable recommending the pork fajitas and chicken enchiladas to anyone, as both were delicious Service was attentive and friendly as well. Thanks for a great meal!

Absolutely AWFUL. The owner of this restaurant should be ashamed of calling this Mexican food. They give you chips and salsa, salsa that is EXACTLY like the bad one you buy at the store, Del Paso and those "mexican food" brands. I asked for carnitas tacos and they literally gave me bbq pulled pork in a tortilla.  I asked for a spicy sauce and they gave me some sour/tart chili paste I've seen Chinese restaurant use. Whoever has rated this place more than one star has clearly never tasted Mexican food in their lives. YUCK.

This has been the worst experience at any restaurant in my life! Appetizers came out after a long wait and all sporadically. My party and I waited an hour and a half after placing our main course and nothing! We spoke to the waiter and he just kept making excuses. The restaurant was not even occupied at that time. After explaining our dissatisfaction, we left without any of us seeing any sort of main course. I recommend this restaurant to people who have 8 hours or more to spare, so that they can receive their food. Will never come back to give this place a chance, I do not want to die waiting for food to come out. 👎
Everytim I come to Bethesda, it's a must have. Please order the carnitas and a side of Yucateca sauce. Your taste buds will love you .
Andrew makes you feel at home! Amazing frozen Marg's and fajitas.
Always great!

Hands down THE best Mexican food I've ever had. And actually one of the best restaurants I've ever been to in general. I once sat here and had about 9 bowls of salsa because it's so damn good. Would have to recommend the steak nachos and Enchiladas Verdes, but you really can't go wrong with anything here.
Been going here since I was a baby ... this place is AMAZING. Great food, delicious margaritas, wonderful staff/ family
(Translated by Google) Good service, acceptable food  (Original) Buena atención,  comida aceptable
The VERY best family-owned restaurant. They use top quality ingredients and prepare the very best cuisine. We always try something different and have not been disappointed.
Not your typical Mexican Restaurant. True Mexican Menu. Home appeal with great customer service. Looking forward to try the rest of the Menu.
The real deal, owned by an actual person. In town since 1980!  They do lovely work. Tasty, hand-crafted food and drinks. Friendly service, not noisy, a feeling of being at home.
Amazing food. Family owned.
Outside patio quaint, intimate. Fabulous guac, even better margaritas!
Excellent food and service.  Love it.

My favorite spot for Mexican so I shouldn't tell you that the Al pastor fajita or tacos are amazing nor should I tell you that their upstairs patio space is wonderful. I love this family run slice of home.
Good food with nice presentation, fair prices and friendly, efficient service.

My favorite family run local mexican restaurant!  I always return when visiting because the food tastes like it was cooked by a grandma, with heaping helpings of love! The mole (unsweet chocolate sauce) is the better here than anywhere I have tried!

Outstanding Mexican food, friendly family-run service. I grew up in California and have generally found East Coast Mexican restaurants to be inferior. Tia Queta is the exception. Truly excellent. Especially the Molé.

I ordered some shrimps a la Mexicana. Only 4 shrimps came in the order, and they didn’t even taste good. I was burping all day after eating there. Maybe other dishes are better, but shrimp is not one of them. On the positive side, service was fast, and chips and salsa were good.

Tia Queta is a family owned restaurant in Bethesda, which makes it pretty rare in it's own right, but overall it's just a nice chill place to come for dinner or a drink.  Whether you're looking for a margarita on the open air patio on a warm summer day or a warming plate of Mexican food on a cold winter night, this place has got you covered.
Can’t beat this Bethesda tradition
I love the ambiance, especially the open air bar area but I was disappointed with the rellenos.  Sorry to say.  Still a favorite spot yo visit with friends.
Best molé around
Authentically delicious. I love this place. Drinks, service, and food are all incredible!
(Translated by Google) Delicious food, we love Tía Queta, we recommend it 100%  (Original) La comida deliciosa, nos encanta Tía Queta, lo recomendamos 100%
A little overpriced, but overall good experience. Service was great and food was impressive. I had tamales, which were good. I’ve had better Mexican food, but not served by white guys in Maryland.

The owner of the restaurant personally served us and for that we felt like VIP guest. The food was authentic and tasty. The best cup of coffee I had in a while. Love the decor... really makes you feel your in Mexico. Gots to try the blackened fish tacos!
This is the only place I get nachos now. Everyone else's are inadequate. Very friendly staff as well.
Ok service last time we were there the Chile Margarita came with all the Chile seeds 😐not cool not nice very horrible experience
Very nice...fair prices. Great mole!!
Authentic Mexican home cooking
Most delicious mexican food I have ever tasted
Nice rooftop, but food and drinks are overpriced for the quality.

Has been around since 1980. I was one of the first customers.  I go back when possible. Great and consistent quality. Excellent hot sauce. Friendly owner and staff. Best Mexican food I have tasted. All other Mexican restaurants I always try to compare with this one.
I heard a MOUSE! Also the food is overpriced. The rice with every meal looks and tastes like it is instant rice.
Best Mexican Restaurant in Bethesda! A must try! Great customer service and authentic food

Family owned and operated,  Tai Queta offers authentic regional Mexican cuisine second to none, including what I've experienced in Mexico, as well as the highly commercial downtown establishments that hand you a device that may vibrate in 45 minutes . It is unlike any other US Mexican restaurant in know. I'don't pay attention to all parts of the menu,  particularly the fish, and always ask about the 'specials--the kitchen likes to experiment. Service is informal, friendly,  and extremely kid-friendly
Good food, great service, pleasant ambiance. We will return 😊
Very authentic but food and drinks are mediocre.
Serrvice was very friendly and portions were large, but dishes were a little uninspired.  Carnitas was just deep fried chunks of pork with a half scoop of bland rice and beans on the side.

I've been here plenty of times but never had a bad day such as the other reviewers. They have no problem deviating from the menu for additional vegetarian options, though they do rice a bit differently so be prepared for that. The upstairs bar is an open area which is really cool during the warmer seasons when it rains.

If there was a negative option I would use it. The cheese was so hard you couldn't even chew it. The chips were cold and tasted store baught and stale. It was ridiculously overpriced, and the service was horrible. There was no hospitality and we had to find someone to come give us refills. In my opinion this family needs to get out of the mexican restaurant buisness.

The avocado relleno had almost no avocado, the fajitas came with almost no cheese, guac or sour cream and the pina colada was terrible! Also the chops were stale
Best  ceviche in the area. Great rooftop. Great central Mexico entrees. Sorry nacho guy this is not a tex-mex place. Try the entomatadas. Wow.
This is my late wife and my favorite place, bar none.  She loved the butterfly shrimp, and I loved the mole bueno. Never disappointed us once.
The rooftop area is a great touch.

ALL OF THE GOOD REVIEWS ARE FROM YEARS AGO!!! Went to Tia Queta today and ordered "nachos especial" (with meat and NO jalapenos- I can't do spicy food. She laughed at me, but I really don't care.) and meat tacos to go. They charged our card ahead of time, and my fiance left to go get wings for himself while I waited for the food. It took 20 minutes, and the cook had to bring it up to the rooftop bar because the waitress was too busy cleaning tables and stocking beer to go get it (the place was empty). She seemed to be sick because she kept coughing all over the place- her hands, the bar, etc. When it arrived, she opened the Styrofoam boxes, quickly shut them and then gave them to me. I checked them.. The tacos were two soggy taquitos- no fresh tomatoes- but tomato sauce on the top, no cheese, just a mysterious white sour cream liquid, and the tortilla hadn't been cooked, as well as some sort of green sauce- who knows... definitely not the way it was described.. She looked at my face and said, "It's tacos" and I said, "These are tacos?" and she replied, scoffing, "Yes!"... Whatever... So I checked the nachos- covered in JALAPENOS- baked into them in the cheese and smothered all over the top.. I said, "I asked for no jalapenos", and she said, "Oh- they add jalapenos?" (remember- she looked at them... they are covering all of the nachos... she knew) I said, "Yes.. I can't eat spicy food." She said- "One second", took my nachos, and PICKED THE JALAPENOS OUT WITH HER HANDS!!! The same hands that cleaned the table, were coughed on, stocked beer!!! She didn't wash them- NOTHING! Then she looked at me, separated the nachos with her hands and said, "See- now it's less spicy". She closed the Styrofoam and HANDED IT TO ME. I was so disgusted and infuriated (these two tiny dishes cost me $20!) I just ran out- I didn't even bother getting my money back. I WILL NEVER GO THERE AGAIN AND I AM CALLING THE HEALTH DEPARTMENT!
